injected the justices into state electoral systems, high school
football games and sexually explicit cable television programming.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, some of the court's most important rulings were
statutory: the invalidation of the Food and Drug Administration's
regulation of tobacco and a decision keeping many medical
malpractice cases against health maintenance organizations out of
federal court.
</P>
<P>
   The HMO decision was unanimous, as were more than a third of the
