<DOCNO> NYT20000701.0148 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-01 17:33 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5289 &Cx1f; var-z
u a BC-SCOTUS-TERM-REVIEW-AR     07-01 0666
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SCOTUS-TERM-REVIEW-ART-2NDTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
  
 WASHINGTON: Ginsburg dissented.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   First Amendment: Religion &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The court ruled 6 to 3 that the practice of organized,
student-led prayer at public high school football games amounted to
an unconstitutional establishment of religion. Stevens wrote the
majority opinion in Santa Fe Independent School District vs. Doe,
No. 99-62. The dissenters were Rehnquist, Scalia and Thomas.
</P>
