<HEADLINE>
MOB BOSS VINCENT GIGANTE CONVALESCING IN FORTH WORTH HOSPITAL
PRISON 
</HEADLINE>
   By TINA KELLEY   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Vincent Gigante, the former boss of the Genovese
crime family who used to roam the streets of the New York's
Greenwich Village wearing pajamas and a robe _ trying to show he
was mentally incompetent to stand trial, according to prosecutors _
is spending his days in a hospital prison in Fort Worth, Texas,
said one of his lawyers, Michael Marinaccio.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's been there for several months now,'' Marinaccio said.
``He has the same health problems he always had.''
</P>
<P>
   Those problems include a heart condition that has required two
open heart surgeries, plus mental health problems, Marinaccio said.
</P>
<P>
   ``The state of his physical health has always been frail, plus
he is suffering from dementia, so they have to monitor him both
physically and psychologically,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Gigante is serving a 12-year prison sentence for racketeering
and murder-conspiracy convictions.
</P>
</TEXT>
