   (NYT2) YOUNSTOWN, Ohio -- July 1, 2000 -- PRISON-EXPERIMENT-2 --
Five prisons operate in Youngstown, Ohio, with about 40,000
inmates. Many of the prisoners are young fathers with plenty of
time to ponder long lists of regrets, with their children, often
little known and less seen, at the top of those lists. At the
Northeastern Ohio Correctional Center, a new social experiment is
