<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-MOTHER-GOOSE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SECRET STATUS ROARS TO WIN IN MOTHER GOOSE 
</HEADLINE>
   By JOSEPH DURSO   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Her name is Secret Status, a daughter of A.P. Indy
and grand-daughter of Seattle Slew and Alydar, and the last time
she ran was two months ago when she charged from 13th place into a
six-length victory in the Kentucky Oaks. Secret Status showed her
powerful closing ability again Saturday when she roared through the
homestretch at Belmont Park to win the Mother Goose, the second
race in the Triple Tiara series for fillies.
</P>
<P>
   The margin was not as great as in the Oaks, but Secret Status
still got there first by the length of her neck over Jostle, who
won the Black-Eyed Susan Stakes at Pimlico. Jostle had a length and
a half on Finder's Fee, who three weeks ago won the Acorn, the
first race in the Triple Tiara.
</P>
<P>
   Still, Secret Status carved out a solid claim to championship
honors for 3-year-old fillies, and her trainer, Neil Howard, said
she would continue her campaign next in the Coaching Club American
Oaks at Belmont on July 22 and in the Alabama at Saratoga on Aug.
19.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had the other fillies measured turning for home,'' said Pat
Day, who has ridden Secret Status five consecutive times. ``But
once we straightened away, she didn't seem too concerned about
putting Jostle away. I gave her a couple of taps and, inside the
sixteenth pole, she really took off.''
</P>
<P>
   Mike Smith, the jockey on Jostle, observed that his filly ``ran
a dynamite race.'' But he added: ``It took a Kentucky Oaks winner
to beat her.''
</P>
<P>
   Shug McGaughey, who trains Finder's Fee, said that she ran a
good race but ``she just wasn't good enough today.''
</P>
<P>
   Secret Status, who is owned by Will Farish, has won six of her
10 starts overall and has finished in the money nine times. She ran
the 1 1/8 miles in 1:48, returned $3.40 for a $2 bet to win and
earned $150,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-01-00 1821EDT &QL; 
